+# ADR 0004 â€” Currency-aware money display formatter (`formatMoney`)
+
+- **Status:** Accepted
+- **Date:** 2026-05-28
+- **Deciders:** Solution Architect
+- **Area:** `src/features/ledger/lib` (money display)
+- **Relates to:** ADR 0003 (money arithmetic), ADR 0002 (currency-aware banker's rounding), ADR 0001 (input-boundary validation)
+
+## Context
+
+ADR 0002 (`roundMoney`) and ADR 0003 (`addMoney`/`subtractMoney`) keep the
+*stored* money value canonical to a currency's minor units, drift-free. But the
+ledger had **no display-side primitive**: any UI rendering a balance would reach
+for `` `$${value}` `` or an ad-hoc `toFixed(2)`, which (a) hard-codes the symbol
+and 2-decimal assumption â€” wrong for JPY (0dp) and BHD (3dp) and for locales that
+place the symbol after the number, and (b) can re-introduce a value that disagrees
+with the stored figure (`toFixed` on a drifted float, or formatting a raw
+`0.1 + 0.2`). The display layer needs a formatter paired with the arithmetic
+stack so *what the user sees is provably what the ledger stored*.
+
+Inspected before deciding: `ledger/lib/round.ts` (`roundMoney`, `minorUnits`,
+`MINOR_UNITS`), `ledger/lib/arithmetic.ts` (`MoneyArithmeticError`, `Money`,
+`MoneyInput`, the `resolveOperand` mixed-currency/non-finite pattern),
+`arithmetic.test.ts`, `ledger/index.ts` (barrel), ADR 0001/0002/0003. No existing
+formatter â€” confirmed via `search_code` over the ledger feature.
+
+## Decision
+
+Add `src/features/ledger/lib/format.ts` exporting
+`formatMoney(value, currency, locale?)`, a tiny pure function built on the ADR
+0002/0003 primitives.
+
+- **`Intl.NumberFormat` (style: "currency")** is authoritative for symbol
+  placement, digit grouping, and minor-unit precision. It is locale- and
+  currency-correct by construction â€” `$1,234.50`, `1.234,56 â‚¬` (de-DE), `ÂĄ1,235`
+  (JPY, zero decimals) â€” so the module hard-codes no symbol or decimal count.
+- **`locale` defaults to `"en-US"`** when omitted.
+- **Normalized through `roundMoney` before formatting.** The value is passed
+  through `roundMoney(value, currency)` (ADR 0002) first, so display reflects the
+  canonical stored value and can never disagree by float drift:
+  `formatMoney(addMoney(0.1, 0.2, "USD"), "USD") === "$0.30"` exactly. This also
+  normalizes `-0 â†’ 0`, so a zero balance never renders as `-$0.00`.
+- **Fail-loud, reusing ADR 0003's typed error.** A non-finite value or a tagged
+  `Money` whose currency differs from the format currency throws a
+  `MoneyArithmeticError` (`.code` `"not-finite"` / `"mixed-currency"`) â€” the same
+  pattern `arithmetic.ts` uses, so a EUR amount is never silently rendered with a
+  USD symbol. A blank/unknown currency throws `RangeError` via
+  `roundMoney`/`minorUnits` (and `Intl`).
+
+Operands accept a bare `number` (assumed in `currency`) or a tagged `Money`,
+mirroring `MoneyInput` from ADR 0003. Exported via the feature barrel
+(`features/ledger/index.ts`), matching the co-located pure-lib convention.
+
+**Why let `Intl` derive fraction digits instead of forcing `minorUnits()`?**
+For standard ISO-4217 codes ICU and our `MINOR_UNITS` table agree (USDâ†’2,
+JPYâ†’0, BHDâ†’3); deferring to `Intl` keeps the formatting locale-correct without a
+second source of truth, and `roundMoney` has already pinned the value to our
+minor-unit table, so the two cannot diverge for stored figures. **Why normalize
+through `roundMoney` rather than trust the caller?** Defense in depth â€” display
+must hold the invariant even if a caller passes an un-rounded intermediate.
+
+## Consequences
+
+- **Positive:** the ledger has one drift-free, currency- and locale-aware money
+  formatter; display is provably consistent with stored value across the ADR 0003
+  arithmetic; corrupt/cross-currency inputs fail loud with the existing typed
+  error; zero new rounding or formatting logic â€” `roundMoney` and `Intl` stay
+  authoritative.
+- **Negative / residual risk:** `Intl.NumberFormat` output depends on the
+  runtime's ICU data; exact strings (symbol, grouping) are ICU-version-sensitive
+  (UNVERIFIED across all deploy targets â€” Node ships full ICU by default and the
+  test runtime confirms the expected strings). For a non-ISO currency code unknown
+  to ICU, `Intl` throws `RangeError` â€” acceptable fail-loud behavior. No
+  per-render `Intl` instance caching yet; negligible for current volumes, revisit
+  if a hot render path appears.
+- **Carried forward:** ADR 0003's deferred N-ary `sumMoney` and ADR 0002 Task 4
+  (`roundToCents â†’ roundMoney` convergence) are unchanged by this ADR.
+
+## Coverage / verification
+
+- `format.test.ts`: 8 tests covering USD default-locale, EUR `de-DE` (comma
+  decimal + trailing â‚¬), JPY (zero minor units), negative values (incl. `-0`),
+  very large values, NaN/Infinity rejection (typed `not-finite`, also catchable as
+  `RangeError`), mixed-currency `Money` rejection (typed `mixed-currency`), and the
+  **Reviewer's end-to-end check** `formatMoney(addMoney(0.1, 0.2, "USD"), "USD")
+  === "$0.30"`.
+- `npm test` â†’ **42/42 pass** (12 amount + 13 round + 9 arithmetic + 8 format).
+- `tsc --noEmit` clean. `eslint` on the changed files clean.
+- **Release gate NOT all-green:** full-repo `eslint .` fails on a **pre-existing**
+  error in `src/app/page.tsx` (`@next/next/no-html-link-for-pages`, introduced by
+  commit `d5f670c`, unrelated to this change). Per the release rule, the
+  post-merge state is not lint-clean â†’ **merge blocked, escalated via
+  manual_review.** This formatter change is complete and lint-clean in isolation.
+- Exported through `features/ledger/index.ts`.
+
+## Task breakdown
+
+1. **`formatMoney(value, currency, locale?)` + `Intl` currency formatting** â€”
+   default locale `en-US`; let `Intl` drive symbol/grouping/precision.
+   *(implemented)* â€” **2 pts**
+2. **Normalize through `roundMoney` before display** â€” canonical-value guarantee
+   + `-0 â†’ 0`. *(implemented)* â€” **1 pt**
+3. **Fail-loud rejection** â€” reuse `MoneyArithmeticError` for non-finite +
+   mixed-currency `Money`; blank currency via `roundMoney`. *(implemented)* â€” **1 pt**
+4. **Unit tests** â€” six required cases + Reviewer consistency check.
+   *(implemented)* â€” **2 pts**
+5. **Barrel export** â€” surface `formatMoney` from `features/ledger/index.ts`.
+   *(implemented)* â€” **1 pt**
+6. **Resolve pre-existing lint error in `src/app/page.tsx`** (replace `<a href="/">`
+   with `next/link` `<Link>`) so the release gate is all-green and this work can
+   merge. *(blocked â€” outside ledger scope; escalated)* â€” **1 pt**
+
+**Total: 8 pts â€” 7 delivered this run, 1 blocking the merge (Task 6, pre-existing).**
